      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The long-term outcome undeniably represents a strategic failure, as the intervention directly contributed to the fragmentation of the Libyan state. By removing Qaddafi without a comprehensive stabilization plan, the operation created a dangerous power vacuum that empowered militias and extremist elements. This instability has not only plagued Libya but has also destabilized the entire North African and Mediterranean region, proving the intervention's geopolitical shortcomings.",
      "source": "target",
