      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While some argue that instability was inevitable, this perspective downplays the direct role the intervention played in accelerating and exacerbating the conflict. The removal of a singular, albeit authoritarian, leader did not automatically lead to a functioning democracy; instead, it unleashed pre-existing tribal and regional rivalries. Therefore, viewing it as merely \"forcing a transition\" ignores the catastrophic breakdown of governance that followed the foreign military action.",
